description: Returns a list of the accessors and their properties. Accessor objects are containers that have the information required for token based access to your Ethereum nodes.

parameters.name: NetworkType
parameters.description: The blockchain network that the Accessor token is created for.

nested_items.name: Accessors
nested_items.description: An array of AccessorSummary objects that contain configuration properties for each accessor.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the accessor.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The current status of the accessor.

nested_items.name: CreationDate
nested_items.description: The creation date and time of the accessor.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the accessor. For more information about ARNs and their format, see Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) in the Amazon Web Services General Reference.

nested_items.name: NetworkType
nested_items.description: The blockchain network that the Accessor token is created for.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The pagination token that indicates the next set of results to retrieve.
